This Zip file contains a bashcript which searches an entire directory recursively for words which you want to find,The scrit is case insentive.
Also it has an calculator app which allows you to use the calculator on the console(terminal) only for division purposes, and the output result goes into a textfile
To use the App:
Unzip the files in a directory and open terminal in same directory, Type in Make to compile the files
After that "./calculator output.txt 10000.0"
The app only does calculation on the division operator and the number should be provided in the second command line argument
You can navigate using the wasd buttons on the keyborad and also you can shuffle the calculator by pressing "e"
I did these projects an year ago so i dont really remember their purpose but i did my best to recall and explain them to you.
